# Data model — `prisma/schema.prisma` is canonical

The Prisma schema in this repo is the single source of truth for the
dashboard's data shape. The scoping doc (§3.1) describes the same entities
but is a living document — when the two disagree, **fix the schema and update
the scoping doc**, not the other way around. Surface the conflict in the PR
description so the human reviewer can confirm.

## Authoritative entities

The dashboard owns authoritatively only:

- `Decision` — append-only program decision log.
- `ExceptionRequest` — §16.3 exception flow (v0.2+).
- `ReclamationEvent` — §4.6.4 idle-credit / unused-seat events (v0.2+).

Every other entity (`User`, `License`, `UsageRecord`, `BudgetSnapshot`, etc.)
is a **mirror** of an authoritative external source — IdP, Deel, gateway,
vendor admin APIs, policy repo. Mirrors must be:

- **Read-mostly.** Writes happen via the upstream system, then reconcile.
- **Reconstructable.** If the dashboard is wiped, the mirror is rebuilt from
  the upstream source. No mirror field can be the only place a value exists.
- **Stamped with provenance.** Every mirror row should record where it came
  from (`License.source`, `UsageRecord` from gateway logs, etc.).

## v0.1 vs canonical

The v0.1 schema (`User`, `License`, `UsageRecord`, `Decision`) is a deliberate
subset. The full canonical schema (scoping §3.1) adds:

- `ExceptionRequest`, `ReclamationEvent` — authoritative, append-only.
- `BudgetSnapshot` — monthly trend table per (product, sub-tier).
- `FrictionBudgetMetric` — §17.5 weekly KPIs.
- The §3.2 SQL views (`v_user_current_posture`, `v_program_health`,
  `v_manager_queue`, `v_cursor_seat_board`, `v_codex_ladder`).

When v0.2 lands these, follow `prisma-changes.mdc` (migration + seed + PR
together) and write a one-line note in the migration explaining which
F-feature it enables.

## Enums vs strings

v0.1 stores `Product`, `LicenseSource`, `UsageDecision`, `DecisionType`,
`UserStatus` as `String` rather than as Prisma enums to keep the prototype
simple. The canonical schema uses real enums. v0.2 should migrate them via
a migration that converts the columns to enum types and updates the seed.
Don't add new enum-shaped fields as `String`; if you're adding new shape,
use a real enum from day one.

## Synthetic data is not authoritative

`lib/synthetic-data.ts` is a deterministic generator for prototype / demo /
test fixtures. It is **not** the data model. If you change the schema, update
the generator to match — but never let the generator's shape drift the schema
the other way (e.g. don't add a field to the schema "because the generator
needs it"; the generator follows the schema, not vice versa).

## Source-of-truth boundary at a glance

| Entity | Authoritative source | Dashboard role |
|---|---|---|
| `User` identity, `managerId` | Azure AD + Deel | mirror; nightly reconcile |
| `User.roleTag` | Deel | mirror; webhook-driven |
| `License` (Cursor) | Cursor admin API + policy repo | mirror; writes go via PR |
| `License` (Codex) | `wdts-ai-policy/policies/*.toml` | mirror; writes go via PR |
| `License` (Claude) | Anthropic admin + policy repo | mirror; writes go via PR |
| `License` (Copilot) | M365 admin centre via Microsoft Graph | mirror; writes via M365 admin |
| `UsageRecord` | Gateway logs | mirror; nightly aggregate import |
| `Decision` | Dashboard | **authoritative**, append-only, exported nightly to WORM Blob |
| `ExceptionRequest` | Dashboard | **authoritative** |
| `ReclamationEvent` | Dashboard (driven by gateway events) | **authoritative** |

If you catch yourself reaching for a write to a mirror entity that isn't
sourced from upstream, stop — the write belongs in a policy-repo PR, not in
the dashboard.
